%I A394464 #10 Mar 27 2026 00:04:00
%S A394464 1,3,8,10,14,42,94,200,430,1026,3208
%N A394464 Number of graceful Prüfer codes on n vertices whose tree is the path graph and whose last element equals 0.
%C A394464 Any labeled tree on n vertices admits a unique Prüfer code. A graceful labeling of a tree on n vertices assigns the labels {0,1,...,n-1} to the vertices such that the induced edge labels (absolute differences of endpoint labels) are exactly {1,2,...,n-1}.
%C A394464 A path graph on n vertices is a tree with exactly two vertices of degree 1 and all other vertices of degree 2.
%D A394464 Douglas B. West, Introduction to Graph Theory, Pearson Education Pte. Ltd, 2002, page 81.
%H A394464 Igor Blokhin, <a href="https://github.com/IgorBlokhin/Graph_Theory">Graph Theory</a> (Python repository).
%F A394464 For n>=4: a(n) = A112362(n) - A394465(n).
%e A394464 a(4)=1, meaning that among all graceful Prüfer codes (of length 2) of path graph on vertices {0,1,2,3}, there are 1 code ending in 0: (2, 0). This code correspond to the graph 1--2--0--3.
%Y A394464 Cf. A112362, A394465.
%K A394464 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A394464 4,2
%A A394464 _Igor Blokhin_, Mar 21 2026
